track_notes: Starting from Truss Gap (Parking here not popular) so suggest established parking place instead at NY 521142. Wainwrights of Selside (LDW-110) and Branstree (LDW-081) visited first. Then TARN CRAG LD-026 and Grey Crag (LDW-118). Head for Harrop Pike then follow the remote valley down above the beck. If you wish to bag some Wainwright Outlyers there are four above you on the way back to Swindale should you wish to stay high. West side Howes and Nabs Moor, east side High Wether Howe and Fewling Stones. Watch out for the Golden Eagle (observed May 2012).
track_title: Tarn Crag to include 3 Wainwrights from Swindale
